One of the best things that sprung from Maven was a standard way to provide Java dependencies to projects via HTTP-based repositories. Not only do we now have the Maven Central repository, but it's almost trivial to set up your own company-wide Maven-compatible repositories using tools like [Nexus|http://nexus.sonatype.org/] or [Artifactory|http://www.jfrog.com/products.php]. Following on from the Maven Publisher plugin, the Release plugin provides everything you need to easily and effectively deploy your project artifacts to such repositories.

Before we look at deployment to one of these remote repositories, let's look at another aspect of Maven: installing artifacts into the local Maven cache.
